---
description: Command "pushme" — commit and push to current branch (or main)
alwaysApply: true
---

# pushme command

When the user says **pushme**:

1. Run `npm run pushme` to commit and push to the current branch (uses **main** if not on a branch, e.g. detached HEAD).
2. If the user provided a commit message (e.g. "pushme fix login"), run `npm run pushme -- "fix login"` so the message is used instead of the default "Update".

The script stages all changes, commits with the given or default message, and pushes to `origin` for the current branch.
